I21Pub. L. 102ÿ09484, div. A, title X, ÿ1A1091, Oct. 23, 1992, 106 Stat. 2519, as amended by Pub. L. 103ÿ0982, title I, ÿ1A104(e)(1)(A), (C), Sept. 21, 1993, 107 Stat. 846; Pub. L. 103ÿ09160, div. A, title XI, ÿ1A1174, Nov. 30, 1993, 107 Stat. 1767; Pub. L. 103ÿ09382, title III, ÿ1A391(T3oK), Oct. 20, 1994, 108 Stat. 4024; Pub. L. 105ÿ0985, div. A, title X, ÿ1A1073(d)(2)(B), Nov. 18, 1997, 111 Stat. 1905, provided that:

I21``(a) T4Program AuthorityK._During fiscal years 1993 through 1995, the Secretary of Defense, acting through the Chief of the National Guard Bureau, may conduct a pilot program to be known as the `National Guard Civilian Youth Opportunities Program'.

I21``(b) T4PurposeK._The purpose of the pilot program is to provide a basis for determining_

I22``(1) whether the life skills and employment potential of civilian youth who cease to attend secondary school before graduating can be significantly improved through military-based training, including supervised work experience in community service and conservation projects, provided by the National Guard; and

I22``(2) whether it is feasible and cost effective for the National Guard to provide military-based training to such youth for the purpose of achieving such improvements.

I21``(c) T4Conduct of the ProgramK._The Secretary of Defense may provide for the conduct of the pilot program in such States as the Secretary considers to be appropriate.

I21``(d) T4Program AgreementsK._(1) To carry out the pilot program in a State, the Secretary of Defense shall enter into an agreement with the Governor of the State or, in the case of the District of Columbia, with the commanding general of the District of Columbia National Guard.

I21``(2) Each agreement under the pilot program shall provide for the Governor or, in the case of the District of Columbia, the commanding general to establish, organize, and administer a National Guard civilian youth opportunities program in the State.

