I12(2) Air transportation in support of Special Olympics.

I12(3) Administrative support services.

I12(4) Technical training services.

I12(5) Emergency medical assistance and services.

I12(6) Communications services.

Q04

I11(c) T4Other Authorized AssistanceK._Facilities and equipment of the National Guard, including military property of the United States issued to the National Guard and General Services Administration vehicles leased to the National Guard, and General Services Administration vehicles leased to the Department of Defense, may be used in connection with providing services to any eligible organization under this section.

I11(d) T4Eligible OrganizationsK._The organizations eligible to receive services under this section are as follows:

I12(1) The Boy Scouts of America.

I12(2) The Girl Scouts of America.

I12(3) The Boys Clubs of America.

I12(4) The Girls Clubs of America.

I12(5) The Young Men's Christian Association.

I12(6) The Young Women's Christian Association.

I12(7) The Civil Air Patrol.

I12(8) The United States Olympic Committee.

I12(9) The Special Olympics.

I12(10) The Campfire Boys.

I12(11) The Campfire Girls.

I12(12) The 4ÿ09H Club.

I12(13) The Police Athletic League.

I12(14) Any other youth or charitable organization designated by the Secretary of Defense.

